Jiangxi to Train 10,000 Music, Art, and Physical Education Teachers for Rural Primary Schools within 3 Years - Xinhua News Agency Xinhua News Agency, Nanchang, May 22 (Reporter Chen Yushan) - Recently, the reporter learned from the Jiangxi Provincial Department of Education that in order to strengthen the teaching force of scarce subjects and achieve balanced development of compulsory education in rural areas, Jiangxi province plans to train one qualified music, art, and physical education teacher each for every rural primary school (townships and below) in the province within three years starting from 2016, totaling 10,000 teachers. It is understood that the trainees are other subject teachers from rural primary schools across Jiangxi province who are under 45 years old and have a basic knowledge of music, art, and physical education, or have the ability to teach these subjects. Through the training, they will master the basic knowledge and teaching skills of music, art, and physical education, update their teaching ideas and concepts, grasp modern teaching methods, improve their subject teaching ability, activity design ability, campus cultural ability, and self-development ability, and build a team of versatile teachers in these areas to alleviate the shortage of rural music, art, and physical education teachers. To ensure the quality and effectiveness of the training, Jiangxi also plans to train one music, art, and physical education teacher each for 100 counties (cities, districts) across the province, totaling 300 trainees, to comprehensively improve their teaching demonstration leadership, teaching and research activity design organization, training, and online workshop construction capabilities, playing a role in teaching, demonstrating, guiding, and supervising.
